# Principles Manifest
# CARL lookup table — maps keywords to architectural principle files.
# Read by j.carl-inject.ts plugin on every UserPromptSubmit.
#
# Format:
#   {KEY}_STATE=active|inactive
#   {KEY}_RECALL=comma, separated, keywords
#   {KEY}_FILE=docs/principles/{file}.md
#   {KEY}_PRIORITY=50          # optional, lower loads first (default 50)
#   {KEY}_ALWAYS=false         # optional, true injects without a keyword match
#
# When a prompt word matches any keyword in _RECALL, the corresponding _FILE
# is injected into the agent's context before it processes the prompt.
#
# This file is a SKELETON: the header above is the format contract, and there
# are intentionally no entries below it. Entries are per-repo — the keywords
# must come from the real vocabulary of the target repo (its domain terms,
# frameworks, and layer names), not from a generic stack. Populate it with
# /j.finish-setup, which reads the repo and codifies the patterns it finds, or
# add entries by hand as you codify decisions.
#
# Every {KEY}_FILE must point to a file that exists — carl-inject silently
# skips a missing target, so a dead entry is a principle that never injects.
# The structural eval "principles manifest declares no dead entries" enforces
# this.
